Looking ahead to future actions and their potential impacts post the initial epidemic phase, we have outlined four possible strategies to be implemented after 90 days (by May 26):
a) Maintain current isolation levels without further intervention;
b) Ease isolation measures and resume normal activities (original network layers and weights);
c) Restart only work-related activities while restoring initial probabilities within the layers; or
d) Intensify isolation by halting remaining work and transport activities.
